<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-636-017  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 636 017.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  Nov 26 1990 v9 n25 p38(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CAD graphics translator gives users a preview. (CarberryTechnology Inc.'s CADleaf 2.0) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Schwartz, Karen D.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Carberry Technology Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   CADleaf 2.0 (CAD software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionComputer-Aided DesignComputer GraphicsGraphics Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>CAD Graphics Translator Gives Users a PreviewandM;Carberry Technology Inc. has introduced an expanded version of itscomputer-aided design graphics translation software that lets users previewfiles before conversion.andM;CADleaf 2.0 with Preview from Carberry of Lowell, Mass., converts InterleafASCII format into Computer Graphics Metafile (CGM) and vice versa.andP;  CADleafincludes 10 filters for users of systems from Interleaf Inc. of Cambridge,Mass., and Sun Microsystems Inc.andM;Preview lets users preview the Initial Graphics Exchange Specification, DataExchange Format, CGM or plot file before conversion.andP;  It gives engineeringand manufacturing managers control over the conversion of CAD designs betweensystems or into publishing format, said Carberry president Patrick Carberry.andM;The Navy is using CADleaf for its Altering Instruction Manuals (AIM) project,which will develop a paperless training system.andM;CADleaf provides a &quot;paperless bridge&quot; between the environments ofengineering, design and publishing, said Lorin Powell, branch manager of ATandamp;TCo.'s Federal Systems Computer Livision.andP;  Powell represents ATandamp;T as the primecontractor to the Navy's Department of Personnel Research and DevelopmentCenter in San Diego.andM;The product's translation capabilities and its portability to the ATandamp;Tplatform sparked the Navy's interest, Powell said.andM;&quot;The Navy's interest in CADleaf was spurred by the product's capabilities inconverting a wide range of CAD system output formats into CGM and PostScriptformat, plus the new, real-time previewing feature,&quot; he said.andP;  &quot;Its readyportability to the ATandamp;T 3B2-600G platform makes it an excellent fit for theAIM project.&quot;andM;With Preview, a user can view any CAD file as the translation process isunder way while the previewed file gets converted to CGM format, Carberrysaid.andP;  Once the file is translated to CGM format, the user can move the fileinto any computer-aided manufacturing or Computer Integrated Manufacturingapplication for inclusion into a manufacturing processing sheet or productdocumentation.andM;&quot;We planned this new feature in response to increasing sensitivity forproductivity and cost savings.andP;  Not only can you now view the conversionprocess taking place, step by step, but you can directly control it,&quot;Carberry said.andM;&quot;As a productivity feature, it saves time andcompute costs typically wastedon a 'wrong' conversion.andP;  As a human factors feature, it gives you thesecurity of knowing exactly where you are in any conversion,&quot; he said.andM;CADleaf 2.0 runs on Sun-2, Sun-3, Sun-4 and 386i systems, Hewlett-Packard Co.andO;HP-Apollo workstations and is being adapted for ATandamp;T 3B2 machines.andP;  It isimmediately available starting at $4,995.andO;</TEXT></DOC>